HEADWORD: Countersway
<hw>Coun"ter*sway`</hw> <pr>(-sw⟦amac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
swaying in a contrary direction; an opposing influence.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>countersway</qex> of restraint, curbing their wild
exorbitance.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counter tenor</ent>⟦br⟧
